SIMPLE: glomerate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glomerate
<hw>Glom"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>glomeratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>glomerare</ets> to glomerate, from
<ets>glomus</ets>. See 3d <er>Glome</er>.]</ety> <def>Gathered together
in a roundish mass or dense cluster; conglomerate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glomerate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Glomerate
<hw>Glom"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Glomerated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Glomerating</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To gather or wind into a ball; to collect
into a spherical form or mass, as threads.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glomeration</ent>⟦br⟧
